USER_TOUR__CONSTRUCTOR_ADD_RAIL: With the help of this button you can add more rails
USER_TOUR__CONSTRUCTOR_DELETE_ROW: As you can see, if you would like to remove the last breaker in the rail, constructor will suggest you to remove a rail too
USER_TOUR__CONSTRUCTOR_EDIT_BREAKER: Press gear button to edit a breaker
USER_TOUR__CONSTRUCTOR_RAIL: Here you can see the simulation of your panel rail and add new breakers to the rail
USER_TOUR__EDIT_BREAKER_DIALOG_ACTIONS: Save or cancel changes in breaker settings
USER_TOUR__EDIT_BREAKER_DIALOG_COLOR: Choose a color for the breaker label order number
USER_TOUR__EDIT_BREAKER_DIALOG_ICON: Choose the icon for the breaker label
USER_TOUR__EDIT_BREAKER_DIALOG_INFO:
Fill the form to setup the current breaker.
Click 'Next' when you are ready
USER_TOUR__HEADER_DOWNLOAD:
And the last but not the least step. You can download or print your labels.
Thank you, for your attention! If you still have any questions, please contact your support
USER_TOUR__HEADER_PREVIEW: Preview will help you to see the result of your work, press it and see how your labels will look like
USER_TOUR__HEADER_SETTINGS: Now we can move to settings of the project, where you will setup main parameters
USER_TOUR__HEADER_START:
Hi! I am glad to see you in the best panel label constructor you have ever seen! Let me introduce you the functionality.
First of all let select a suitable language
USER_TOUR__PREVIEW_DIALOG_CONTENT: Here it is! Check, please, is everything ok, and does it meet your expectations
USER_TOUR__PREVIEW_DIALOG_CLOSE: To get back to constructor and fix something, if it is needed, just close the preview
USER_TOUR__ROW_DELETE_BREAKER: Here you can delete wrong or useless breaker if you want. Let's try
USER_TOUR__SETTINGS_BREAKER_QUANTITY:
Now select how much breakers you will have in one rail.
Click 'Next' when you are ready
USER_TOUR__SETTINGS_FONT:
Here you can select a font for your labels.
Click 'Next' when you are ready
USER_TOUR__SETTINGS_LABEL_SIZE:
This field allows you to manage label height.
Click 'Next' when you are ready
USER_TOUR__SETTINGS_PRINT_ORIENTATION: These options will let you select the print page orientation
USER_TOUR__SETTINGS_SEPERATED_UNITED: Choose how would you like to print your labels, should they be united to one rail label, or separated one by one?
USER_TOUR__SETTINGS_SAVE: When general setting are ready we can save them and move on to the constructor
USER_TOUR__SETTINGS_SIZE:
With this fields you can manage breaker size.
Click 'Next' when you are ready
USER_TOUR__SETTINGS_SIZE_TYPE: Here you need to choose what size are you going to setup, the size of the one breaker, or the size of the rail.
USER_TOUR__SETTINGS_TYPE:
Here you can choose the type of the breaker.
Click 'Next' when you are ready
